snippet.textDisplay: I was young, maybe 3rd grade. We were poor -- I had an allowance of $2 a week if I was lucky. I saved for months and months and months until I was finally able to purchase both a Gameboy Pocket and a Pokemon Blue Version. Not only the first major financial achievement of my life, but the game that I have the deepest and most fond memories of. The first time I heard this song was one of the most magical moments of my childhood, and the power that this music holds to me cannot be matched. *tear*

snippet.textDisplay: The first town of the first Pokemon game, where it all started. With its 3 houses, I'm not even sure you could call it a town though. :P Playing this game for the first time back in the days is a feeling I'll surely miss, picking Bulbasaur because I liked the color green and going off on an unknown and exciting portable adventure. I remember playing at night under the sheets with my Worm Light attachment.
